criteria.textblock:
        Inclusion Criteria:

          1. 18-75 years old, no gender limit;

          2. The subject voluntarily cooperated with the research and signed an informed consent
             form;

          3. Meet any of the following three criteria:

               -  Patients with asthma, the standard diagnosis of asthma complied with the GINA
                  2019; ② Patients with COPD, the standard diagnosis of COPD complied with GOLD
                  2019; ③ The subjects in the healthy control group had normal vital capacity
                  (baseline FEV1≥80% of the predicted value, FEV1/FVC was greater than the Lower
                  Limit of Normal, and with negative result of BPT or BDT).

        Exclusion Criteria:

          1. History of other lung diseases, such as cystic fibrosis, bronchiolitis obliterans,
             tuberculosis, lung cancer, etc.;

          2. After taking corticosteroid therapy in the last 4 weeks, respiratory tract infection
             occurred within 8 weeks;

          3. A history of myocardial infarction and stroke in the past 3 months; a history of
             severe arrhythmia, severe cardiac insufficiency, and unstable angina in the past 4
             weeks, etc.;

          4. In the past 4 weeks, severe hemoptysis and epileptic seizures require medication;
             severe hyperthyroidism;

          5. Pregnant women;

          6. Other researchers consider it inappropriate.
